where handleError takes the exception as the argument.

You dont seem to do anything else so you can just combine them both into a single exception


    }catch(Exception e){
    
    }

which will catch everything but you have MUCH less control over the error handling.

A general principle of exceptions is that they are handled at the point they are best abled to  be handled.

You seem to have very disparate exceptions and presumably a TCP exception thrown somewhere in the code is not the same as the SQLException thrown when connecting to a database (I might be wrong here since I don&#39;t know what the rest of the code looks like). So would not a set of exception handlers, one for each type make more sense. Also to reite from Bryan Roach, text disambiguation is not a good idea.

